  "text": "Patients with ischemic cardiomyopathy undergoing mitral procedures have a five-year mortality of approximately 50% [CITATION_1] . Recurrence of CHF occurs in one-third of patients by five years and is the most common cause of death, presumably related to continuing dysfunction of the unmodified ventricle [CITATION_2] .",
